      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It sounds like you might have residual transfer material or improperly seated new pads, which is common after replacement. First, try letting the brakes \"bed in\" following the manufacturer's guidelines to ensure the new pads seat correctly. If the noise persists after bedding in, inspect the pads again to confirm they are fully seated and check the rotor surface for any obvious damage.",
