    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i tried beddin them in but the squeal is still there. it's almost like a constant shrill sound when i'm decelerating, not just a single chirp. i haven't seen any actual wear indicators or lights on the dash yet. could it be the caliper might be sticking a bit?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A constant, high-pitched shrill after bedding in often points to the pads or hardware, but a sticking caliper is definitely possible. Have a friend observe the caliper while you gently apply the brakes to see if one pad is dragging more than the other. If that doesn't reveal anything, you could check that the caliper slide pins are clean, lubricated, and moving freely, as dried-out pins can cause subtle sticking.",
      "source": "target",
